Problem Definition¶

Content The CSV file includes a hourly/daily summary for Szeged, Hungary area, between 2006 and 2016.

Attributes:

  • time
  • summary
  • precipType
  • temperature
  • apparentTemperature
  • humidity
  • windSpeed
  • windBearing
  • visibility
  • loudCover
  • pressure

Objective:

We will predict the Temperature of a given point of time based on the all other attributes affecting the change in T.

1) Predict temp. in 2016 by data of from 2006 to 2015¶

In [26]:
# for minibatch gradient descent
def minibatch(x, y, batch_size = None):
    idx = np.random.choice(len(x), batch_size, replace=False)
    return x[idx], y[idx]
In [27]:
until_15 = X[X['YEAR' ] != 16].index
pred_16 = X[X['YEAR' ] == 16].index
In [28]:
X_train, y_train = X_std[until_15], Y[until_15]
X_test, y_test = X_std[pred_16], Y[pred_16]

print('Training data size:',X_train.shape, y_train.shape)
print('Test data size:',X_test.shape, y_test.shape)

Training data size: (87669, 10) (87669, 1)
Test data size: (8784, 10) (8784, 1)

n_hidden1 = 100

In [30]:
%%time

tf.reset_default_graph()

x = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, [None, n_input])
y = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, [None, n_output])
lr = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)

"""
build a ANN model with two hidden layers (num. of nodes of first hidden layer = 100, num. of nodes of 2nd hidden layer  = 50)







"""

pred = base_model(x, weights, biases)
loss = tf.square(pred - y)
loss = tf.reduce_mean(loss)
optm = tf.train.AdamOptimizer(lr).minimize(loss)


n_batch = 64    # Batch Size
n_iter = 10000   # Learning Iteration
n_prt = 100    # Print Cycle
LR = 0.001

init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
sess = tf.Session()
sess.run(init)

loss_record_train = []
loss_record_valid = []

for epoch in range(n_iter):
    train_x, train_y = minibatch(X_train, y_train, n_batch)
    sess.run(optm, feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y, lr: LR}) 
    
    if epoch % n_prt == 0:
        valid_x, valid_y = minibatch(X_test, y_test, n_batch)
        cost, score = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y})
        cost_v, score_v = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: valid_x, y: valid_y})
        
        loss_record_train.append(cost)
        loss_record_valid.append(cost_v)
        
        print ("Iter {:05d} || train_loss: {:.4f} || valid_loss: {:.4f} ".format(epoch, cost, cost_v))

%%time

tf.reset_default_graph()

"""
build the base model that you builded above again.




"""

pred = base_model(x, weights, biases)
loss = tf.square(pred - y)
loss = tf.reduce_mean(loss)
optm = tf.train.AdamOptimizer(lr).minimize(loss)

n_batch = 64    # Batch Size
n_iter = 10000   # Learning Iteration
n_prt = 100    # Print Cycle
LR = 0.001

init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
sess = tf.Session()
sess.run(init)

loss_record_train = []
loss_record_valid = []

for epoch in range(n_iter):
    train_x, train_y = minibatch(X_train, y_train, n_batch)
    sess.run(optm, feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y, lr: LR}) 
    
    if epoch % n_prt == 0:
        valid_x, valid_y = minibatch(X_test, y_test, n_batch)
        cost, score = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y})
        cost_v, score_v = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: valid_x, y: valid_y})
        
        loss_record_train.append(cost)
        loss_record_valid.append(cost_v)
        
        print ("Iter {:05d} || train_loss: {:.4f} || valid_loss: {:.4f} ".format(epoch, cost, cost_v))

3) Transfer Learning¶

Recall: RH regression¶

  • Code
n_input = 13
n_hidden1 = 100
n_hidden2 = 50
n_output = 1

weights = {
    'hidden1' : tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([n_input, n_hidden1], stddev = 0.1), name = 'w_hidden1'),
    'hidden2' : tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([n_hidden1, n_hidden2], stddev = 0.1), name = 'w_hidden2'),
    'output' : tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([n_hidden2, n_output], stddev = 0.1), name = 'w_output')
}

biases = {
    'hidden1' : tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([n_hidden1], stddev = 0.1), name = 'b_hidden1'),
    'hidden2' : tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([n_hidden2], stddev = 0.1), name = 'b_hidden2'),
    'output' : tf.Variable(tf.random_normal([n_output], stddev = 0.1), name = 'b_output')
}

n_batch = 64   
n_iter = 30000  
n_prt = 100    
LR = 0.001

saver = tf.train.Saver()

init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
sess = tf.Session()
sess.run(init)

loss_record_train = []
loss_record_valid = []

for epoch in range(n_iter):
    train_x, train_y = minibatch(X_train, y_train, n_batch)
    sess.run(optm, feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y, lr: LR}) 

    if epoch % n_prt == 0:
        valid_x, valid_y = minibatch(X_test, y_test, n_batch)
        cost, score = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y})
        cost_v, score_v = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: valid_x, y: valid_y})

        loss_record_train.append(cost)
        loss_record_valid.append(cost_v)

        print ("Iter {:05d} || train_loss: {:.4f} || valid_loss: {:.4f} ".format(epoch, cost, cost_v))

saver.save(sess, './model/rh_reg_ANN')

Training¶

- hidden2 and output layer are initialized with the weights of the RH model

In [40]:
# %%time

tf.reset_default_graph()

test_graph = tf.Graph()
with test_graph.as_default():
    sess = tf.Session(graph = test_graph)
    loader = tf.train.import_meta_graph('./model/rh_reg_ANN' + '.meta')
    loader.restore(sess, './model/rh_reg_ANN')
    
    w_hidden1 = test_graph.get_tensor_by_name('w_hidden1:0')
    w_hidden2 = test_graph.get_tensor_by_name('w_hidden2:0')
    w_output = test_graph.get_tensor_by_name('w_output:0')
    
    b_hidden1 = test_graph.get_tensor_by_name('b_hidden1:0')
    b_hidden2 = test_graph.get_tensor_by_name('b_hidden2:0')
    b_output = test_graph.get_tensor_by_name('b_output:0')

    n_input = 10
    n_hidden1 = 100
    n_hidden2 = 50
    n_output = 1

    """
    replace weights and biases in the hidden2 and output layer with the weights of the RH model 
    
    
    
    
    
    """

    x = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, [None, n_input])
    y = tf.placeholder(tf.float32, [None, n_output])
    lr = tf.placeholder(tf.float32)

    # Define Network
    def transferred_model(x, weights, biases):

        for i in range(1, 3):
            if i == 1:
                hidden = tf.add(tf.matmul(x, weights['hidden{}'.format(i)]), biases['hidden{}'.format(i)])
                hidden = tf.nn.relu(hidden)
            else:
                hidden = tf.add(tf.matmul(hidden, weights['hidden{}'.format(i)]), biases['hidden{}'.format(i)])
                hidden = tf.nn.relu(hidden)

        output = tf.add(tf.matmul(hidden, weights['output']), biases['output'])

        return output

    pred = transferred_model(x, weights, biases)
    loss = tf.square(pred - y)
    loss = tf.reduce_mean(loss)
    optm = tf.train.AdamOptimizer(lr).minimize(loss)

    n_batch = 64    # Batch Size
    n_iter = 10000   # Learning Iteration
    n_prt = 100    # Print Cycle
    LR = 0.001

    init = tf.global_variables_initializer()
    sess.run(init)

    loss_record_train = []
    loss_record_valid = []

    for epoch in range(n_iter):
        train_x, train_y = minibatch(X_train, y_train, n_batch)
        sess.run(optm, feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y, lr: LR}) 

        if epoch % n_prt == 0:
            valid_x, valid_y = minibatch(X_test, y_test, n_batch)
            cost, score = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: train_x, y: train_y})
            cost_v, score_v = sess.run([loss, pred], feed_dict = {x: valid_x, y: valid_y})

            loss_record_train.append(cost)
            loss_record_valid.append(cost_v)

            print ("Iter {:05d} || train_loss: {:.4f} || valid_loss: {:.4f} ".format(epoch, cost, cost_v))
        
# saver.save(sess, './model/rh_reg_ANN')

tr_15_pred = sess.run(pred, feed_dict = {x: X_test})
tr_15_rmse =np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, tr_15_pred))  

plt.figure(figsize = (16, 10))
plt.title("Regression of Temperature (C) in 2016", fontsize = 20)
plt.plot(np.ravel(tr_15_pred),  'r.',   alpha = 0.7, label = 'Transferred ANN: {:.3f}'.format(tr_15_rmse))
plt.plot(np.ravel(y_test), 'k.',  linewidth = 3, alpha = 0.5,  label = 'Actual Values')
plt.legend(loc = 4, fontsize = 15)
plt.ylabel("Temperature (C)", fontsize = 15)
plt.grid(alpha = 0.3)
plt.show()

idx = np.argsort(y_test[:, 0])
